cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper presents a neural network compression algorithm that sparsifies the parameters of a trained fully-connected neural network. The paper focuses on the theoretical analysis of the algorithm and establishes guarantees on the size and accuracy of the resulting compressed network. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also introduces a novel notion of sensitivity and extends traditional coreset constructions, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
